      "type": "story",
      "title": "Against Nature",
      "text": "“It was just a colour out of space—a frightful messenger from unformed realms of infinity beyond all Nature as we know it; from realms whose mere existence stuns the brain and numbs us with the black extra-cosmic gulfs it throws open before our frenzied eyes.”\n<i>– H. P. Lovecraft, “The Colour Out of Space”</i>"
